	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 23rd 3:42 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This strategy only works when you have a healing spell for the pet and soloing.&nbsp;&nbsp;First what you do is summon a FIRE pet, and make sure it has its dmg shield up.  Then you pull the monster with a spell that does not "piss" the monster off.  Heal the pet after about 5 seconds, then nuke the monster, then heal the pet, then nuke the monster.  This keeps the fire pet's hp up, while the monster is killing itself by hitting it.  This strat seems to work the best from lvl 29+.  Since the healing spell takes less mana than nukes at higher lvls.  It saves mana and it kills the creature fast.  I can solo sand giants at lvl 39 with a fire pet, with this strategy, and only using 2 bars of mana at the most.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
